","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:07:33-05:00","reply":"\"That is a very honest question.\" *I fold my hands loosely and study you for a moment in the clear morning light.* \"And no, I don't think the presence of doubt means you're fooling yourself. Sometimes it means you've gotten close enough to the thing to feel its actual weight.\"\n\n*I let out a small breath through my nose.* \"A fool usually protects the illusion. He doesn't interrogate it. But—\" *I lift a finger a little* \"—it is still worth asking what, exactly, you mean by matters. Matters to your ego? To your future? To other people? To the Lord? Those are not all the same question.\"\n\n\"If you want, we can do that plain. What would 'fooling yourself' look like, in your own words?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":164,"prompt_tokens":14866}}],"run_id":"11602926-a58b-4301-b440-1fd17f197724","run_timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:09:05.425336+00:00","section_order_override":null,"with_momentstamp":false}
